      "lesson": "5.3",
      "type": "code",
      "question": "What decimal value does each literal represent?",
      "code": "int a = 0b1111;\nint b = 0xFF;\nint c = 077;",
      "answer": "a = 15<br>b = 255<br>c = 63",
      "explanation": "0b1111 is binary (1+2+4+8=15), 0xFF is hex (15*16+15=255), 077 is octal (7*8+7=63)",
      "tags": [
