    {
      "id": "ch5_5_3_007",
      "lesson": "5.3",
      "type": "basic",
      "front": "Why should you avoid using octal literals (starting with 0)?",
      "back": "It's easy to accidentally create an octal literal by adding a leading zero, which can cause unexpected values. For example, 077 is 63 in decimal, not 77.",
